  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What profitable business I can start with INR 1 lakh?",
  "response": "Starting a business with INR 1 lakh can be quite feasible, especially if you choose the right niche and manage your resources effectively. Here are several profitable business ideas you can consider:\n\n1. **E-commerce Store**: Start a small online store using platforms like Shopify or WooCommerce. You can sell niche products, handmade goods, or dropship items.\n\n2. **Food Truck or Catering**: If you enjoy cooking, consider starting a small food truck or catering service. Focus on a specific cuisine or type of food that is popular in your area.\n\n3. **Digital Marketing Services**: If you have skills in social media management, SEO, or content creation, you can offer your services to small businesses looking to enhance their online presence.\n\n4. **Fitness Coaching**: With a certification in personal training or fitness, you can offer coaching services, either online or in-person. You can also create fitness-related content on social media to attract clients.\n\n5. **Home Cleaning Services**: Start a home cleaning business. This requires minimal investment in cleaning supplies and can be marketed through local online groups, flyers, or word of mouth.\n\n6. **Mobile Car Wash**: A mobile car wash service requires minimal startup costs and can yield a good profit margin. You can operate it from your vehicle and move from one location to another.\n\n7. **Tutoring or Online Courses**: If you are knowledgeable in a particular subject, consider offering tutoring services or creating online courses. You can use platforms like Udemy or Teachable to reach a wider audience.\n\n8. **Event Planning or Decoration**: Start an event planning service or a decoration business for weddings and parties. You can begin small and expand as you gain clients.\n\n9. **Subscription Box Service**: Curate niche products and create a subscription box service. This could be anything from beauty products to snacks or books.\n\n10. **Freelance Services**: If you have skills such as graphic design, writing, or programming, consider freelancing. Websites like Upwork and Fiverr can help you get started.\n\n11. **Mobile Repair Services**: If you have technical skills, start a mobile repair service for smartphones and gadgets. This can be done from home or at client locations.\n\n12. **Plant Nursery or Gardening Services**: With the increasing interest in home gardening, you could start a small plant nursery or offer gardening services.\n\n13. **Content Creation**: Start a YouTube channel, blog, or podcast around a topic you are passionate about. Monetization can come through advertising, sponsorships, or affiliate marketing.\n\n14. **Local Tourism Services**: If you live in an area that attracts tourists, consider offering guided tours, experiences, or local insights.\n\n15. **Health and Wellness Coaching**: If you have expertise in nutrition or wellness, you can offer consultation services to help clients improve their health.\n\nAs with any business, it's important to conduct thorough market research, understand your target audience, and develop a solid business plan before starting. Additionally, consider keeping a buffer in your budget to cover unforeseen expenses that may arise in the initial stages.",
